00:16:11.401 --> 00:16:13.069
Son...

248
00:16:14.277 --> 00:16:18.669
This is the last straw, Amphitryon!

249
00:16:19.231 --> 00:16:20.778
That boy is a menace!

250
00:16:20.868 --> 00:16:23.538
He's too dangerous
to be around normal people!

251
00:16:25.301 --> 00:16:27.415
He didn't mean any harm.
He's just a kid.

252
00:16:27.499 --> 00:16:31.170
He just can't control his strength.

253
00:16:31.253 --> 00:16:33.041
I'm warning you.

254
00:16:33.131 --> 00:16:37.119
You keep that freak away from here!

255
00:16:37.206 --> 00:16:39.712
Freak! Yeah, go away!

256
00:16:51.465 --> 00:16:56.292
Son, you shouldn't let those
things they said back there get to you.

257
00:16:56.578 --> 00:17:01.482
But, Pop, they're right. I am a freak.
I try to fit in. I really do.

258
00:17:01.971 --> 00:17:03.965
I just can't.

259
00:17:05.087 --> 00:17:10.590
Sometimes I feel like
I really don't belong here,

260
00:17:11.637 --> 00:17:15.310
like I'm supposed to be someplace else.

261
00:17:16.192 --> 00:17:18.185
Hercules, son...

262
00:17:18.269 --> 00:17:20.143
I know it doesn't make any sense.

263
00:17:30.531 --> 00:17:35.522
<i>I have often dreamed of a far off place</i>

264
00:17:35.604 --> 00:17:40.792
<i>Where a great warm welcome
will be waiting for me</i>

265
00:17:40.878 --> 00:17:45.749
<i>Where the crowds will cheer
when they see my face</i>

266
00:17:45.830 --> 00:17:51.376
<i>And a voice keeps sayin'
this is where I'm meant to be</i>

267
00:17:52.062 --> 00:17:54.807
<i>I will find my way</i>

268
00:17:54.898 --> 00:17:57.164
<i>I can go the distance</i>

269
00:17:57.254 --> 00:17:59.881
<i>I'll be there someday</i>

270
00:17:59.971 --> 00:18:02.161
<i>If I can be strong</i>

271
00:18:02.248 --> 00:18:04.602
<i>I know every mile</i>

272
00:18:04.764 --> 00:18:07.716
<i>Will be worth my while</i>

273
00:18:08.639 --> 00:18:14.904
<i>I would go most anywhere to feel like I</i>

274
00:18:15.389 --> 00:18:19.215
<i>Belong</i>

275
00:18:22.459 --> 00:18:24.094
Hercules,

276
00:18:24.177 --> 00:18:29.244
there's something your mother and I
have been meaning to tell ya.

277
00:18:29.330 --> 00:18:33.121
But if you found me,
then where did I come from?

278
00:18:33.205 --> 00:18:35.079
Why was I left here?

279
00:18:35.801 --> 00:18:40.313
This was around your neck
when we found you.

280
00:18:41.673 --> 00:18:44.059
It's the symbol of the gods.

281
00:18:44.628 --> 00:18:47.897
This is it! Don't you see?
Maybe they have the answers!

282
00:18:47.985 --> 00:18:49.739
I'll go to the temple of Zeus and...

283
00:18:52.338 --> 00:18:54.932
Ma, Pop,

284
00:18:55.573 --> 00:18:59.006
you're the greatest parents
anyone could have, but...

285
00:19:00.247 --> 00:19:01.762
I gotta know.

286
00:19:19.740 --> 00:19:22.606
<i>I am on my way</i>

287
00:19:22.696 --> 00:19:24.647
<i>I can go the distance</i>

288
00:19:24.733 --> 00:19:27.327
<i>I don't care how far</i>

289
00:19:27.449 --> 00:19:29.639
<i>Somehow, I'll be strong</i>

290
00:19:29.726 --> 00:19:32.037
<i>I know every mile</i>

291
00:19:32.123 --> 00:19:35.512
<i>Will be worth my while</i>

292
00:19:35.598 --> 00:19:38.551
<i>I would go most anywhere</i>

293
00:19:38.634 --> 00:19:44.704
<i>To find where I belong</i>

294
00:20:02.601 --> 00:20:04.508
Oh, mighty Zeus,

295
00:20:04.598 --> 00:20:08.630
please, hear me and answer my prayer.

296
00:20:08.713 --> 00:20:10.499
I need to know.

297
00:20:10.589 --> 00:20:11.941
Who am I?

298
00:20:12.028 --> 00:20:14.414
Where do I belong?

299
00:20:20.176 --> 00:20:21.134
Huh?

300
00:20:26.727 --> 00:20:28.558
My boy.

301
00:20:28.646 --> 00:20:30.716
My little Hercules.

302
00:20:31.281 --> 00:20:33.068
Ahhhh!

303
00:20:33.597 --> 00:20:36.191
Hey, hey, hey. Hold on, kiddo!

304
00:20:36.274 --> 00:20:37.342
What's your hurry?

305
00:20:37.432 --> 00:20:41.223
After all these years, is this the kind of
hello you give your father?

306
00:20:42.586 --> 00:20:43.698
Father?

307
00:20:43.783 --> 00:20:46.650
Didn't know you had a famous father,
did you?

308
00:20:46.740 --> 00:20:49.245
Surprise!

309
00:20:49.656 --> 00:20:51.606
Look how you've grown.

310
00:20:51.693 --> 00:20:57.119
Why, you've got your mother's
beautiful eyes and my strong chin. Hah!

311
00:20:57.764 --> 00:20:59.279
I don't understand.

312
00:20:59.362 --> 00:21:03.230
If you're my father,
that would make me a...

313
00:21:03.316 --> 00:21:06.345
- A god.
- A god.

314
00:21:06.433 --> 00:21:07.424
A god!

315
00:21:07.511 --> 00:21:09.026
Hey, you wanted answers,

316
00:21:09.109 --> 00:21:12.453
and by thunder, you're old enough
now to know the truth.

317
00:21:12.543 --> 00:21:15.976
But why did you leave me on Earth?
Didn't you want me?

318
00:21:16.099 --> 00:21:17.570
Of course we did.

319
00:21:17.657 --> 00:21:20.489
Your mother and I
loved you with all our hearts.

320
00:21:20.572 --> 00:21:24.081
Someone stole you from us
and turned you mortal,

321
00:21:24.168 --> 00:21:27.033
and only gods
can live on Mount Olympus.

322
00:21:27.523 --> 00:21:28.950
And you can't do a thing?

323
00:21:29.041 --> 00:21:30.992
I can't, Hercules, but you can.

324
00:21:31.078 --> 00:21:34.031
Really? What? I'll do anything.

325
00:21:34.114 --> 00:21:37.263
Hercules, if you can prove yourself
a true hero on Earth,

326
00:21:37.349 --> 00:21:39.256
your godhood will be restored!

327
00:21:39.346 --> 00:21:41.657
A true hero. Great!

328
00:21:42.263 --> 00:21:45.608
Exactly how do you
become a true hero?

329
00:21:45.698 --> 00:21:50.001
First, you must seek out Philoctetes,
the trainer of heroes.

330
00:21:50.092 --> 00:21:52.925
Seek out Philoctetes.
Right. I'll... Whoa!

331
00:21:53.008 --> 00:21:54.959
Whoa! Hold your horses!

332
00:21:55.045 --> 00:21:56.832
Which reminds me.

333
00:22:02.474 --> 00:22:03.542
Ha ha!

334
00:22:03.633 --> 00:22:08.504
You probably don't remember Pegasus,
but you two go way back, son.

335
00:22:15.936 --> 00:22:17.722
Oh, Pegasus!

336
00:22:18.093 --> 00:22:22.964
He's a magnificent horse
with the brain of a bird.

337
00:22:23.206 --> 00:22:24.437
Huh?

338
00:22:24.604 --> 00:22:27.591
I'll find Philoctetes
and become a true hero.

339
00:22:27.680 --> 00:22:28.954
That's the spirit!

340
00:22:29.038 --> 00:22:30.509
I won't let you down, Father!

341
00:22:31.674 --> 00:22:32.665
Yee-haw!

342
00:22:33.471 --> 00:22:35.302
Good luck, son.

343
00:22:37.906 --> 00:22:40.499
<i>I will beat the odds</i>

344
00:22:40.582 --> 00:22:42.292
<i>I can go the distance</i>

345
00:22:42.380 --> 00:22:44.766
<i>I will face the world</i>

346
00:22:44.856 --> 00:22:46.763
<i>Fearless, proud and strong</i>

347
00:22:46.853 --> 00:22:49.119
<i>I will please the gods</i>

348
00:22:49.210 --> 00:22:50.964
<i>I can go the distance</i>

349
00:22:51.048 --> 00:22:56.790
<i>Till I find my hero's welcome
right where I</i>

350
00:22:56.920 --> 00:23:03.587
<i>Belong</i>

351
00:23:29.514 --> 00:23:31.105
Whoa!

352
00:23:34.148 --> 00:23:35.695
You sure this is the right place?

353
00:23:46.610 --> 00:23:49.803
What's the matter, little guy?
You stuck?

354
00:23:49.885 --> 00:23:51.401
Hey, butt out, buddy!

355
00:23:51.564 --> 00:23:52.795
Ugh!

356
00:23:53.001 --> 00:23:55.714
Girls! Stop! Stop!
Come back, come back, come back.

357
00:23:55.837 --> 00:23:58.028
Whoa, whoa! Oh. Geez!

358
00:23:58.473 --> 00:24:01.580
Whoa, whoa, whoa! Oh, Nymphs!

359
00:24:02.189 --> 00:24:04.901
- They can't keep their hands off me.
- Hey!

360
00:24:08.861 --> 00:24:11.531
What's the matter?
You never seen a satyr before?

361
00:24:11.617 --> 00:24:13.523
Uh, no. Can you help us?

362
00:24:13.613 --> 00:24:17.122
We're looking for someone
called Philoctetes.

363
00:24:18.127 --> 00:24:19.402
Cali me Phil.

364
00:24:19.486 --> 00:24:20.792
- Phil!
- Ow!

365
00:24:20.883 --> 00:24:23.357
Boy, am I glad to meet you!
I'm Hercules.

366
00:24:23.439 --> 00:24:25.749
This is Pegasus.

367
00:24:27.234 --> 00:24:29.348
Animals! Disgusting!

368
00:24:29.431 --> 00:24:30.946
I need your help.

369
00:24:31.030 --> 00:24:33.023
I want to become a hero, a true hero.

370
00:24:34.943 --> 00:24:37.689
- Sorry, kid. Can't help ya.
- Wait!

371
00:24:38.658 --> 00:24:39.694
Uh, sorry.

372
00:24:39.777 --> 00:24:44.200
- Why not?
- Two words, I am retired.

373
00:24:45.289 --> 00:24:47.077
Look, I gotta do this.

374
00:24:47.167 --> 00:24:48.802
Haven't you ever had a dream,

375
00:24:48.884 --> 00:24:51.477
something you wanted so bad
you'd do anything?

376
00:24:54.197 --> 00:24:57.390
Kid, come inside.
I want to show you something.

377
00:25:05.302 --> 00:25:08.288
Watch it!
That was part of the mast of the Argo.

378
00:25:08.377 --> 00:25:10.044
- The Argo?
- Yeah.

379
00:25:10.134 --> 00:25:12.248
Who do you think
taught Jason how to sail?

380
00:25:12.332 --> 00:25:13.564
Cleopatra?

381
00:25:13.651 --> 00:25:16.005
I trained all those would-be heroes.

382
00:25:16.126 --> 00:25:20.713
Odysseus, Perseus, Theseus.
A lot of "yeuseus."

383
00:25:20.799 --> 00:25:24.951
And every single one of those bums
let me down flatter than a discus.

384
00:25:25.034 --> 00:25:27.421
None of 'em could go the distance.

385
00:25:28.110 --> 00:25:30.780
And then there was Achilles.

386
00:25:30.946 --> 00:25:34.814
Now, there was a guy who had it all,
the build, the foot speed.

387
00:25:34.900 --> 00:25:39.128
He could jab, he could take a hit,
he could keep on comin'.

388
00:25:39.215 --> 00:25:41.764
But that furshlugginer heel of his!

389
00:25:41.852 --> 00:25:44.641
He barely gets nicked there once
and kaboom!

390
00:25:45.127 --> 00:25:46.598
He's history.

391
00:25:48.521 --> 00:25:50.232
Yeah, I had a dream once.

392
00:25:50.318 --> 00:25:53.665
I dreamed I was gonna train
the greatest hero there ever was.

393
00:25:53.755 --> 00:25:59.781
So great, the gods would hang a picture
of him in the stars all across the sky,

394
00:25:59.867 --> 00:26:02.972
and people would say,
"That's Phil's boy."

395
00:26:03.061 --> 00:26:04.892
That's right.

396
00:26:04.979 --> 00:26:06.689
Eh, but dreams are for rookies.

397
00:26:06.776 --> 00:26:08.847
A guy can only take
so much disappointment.

398
00:26:08.934 --> 00:26:11.124
But I'm different than
those other guys, Phil!

399
00:26:11.210 --> 00:26:13.596
I can go the distance.
Come on. I'll show you.

400
00:26:14.884 --> 00:26:16.878
Geez! You don't give up, do ya?

401
00:26:17.121 --> 00:26:18.397
Watch this.

402
00:26:22.675 --> 00:26:24.548
Holy Hera.

403
00:26:24.631 --> 00:26:27.901
You know, maybe if I...
No! Snap out of it!

404
00:26:27.988 --> 00:26:30.014
I'm too old
to get mixed up in this stuff again.

405
00:26:30.104 --> 00:26:34.255
But if I don't become a true hero, I'll
never be able to rejoin my father, Zeus.

406
00:26:34.698 --> 00:26:35.689
Hold it!

407
00:26:35.776 --> 00:26:37.803
Zeus is your father, right?

408
00:26:37.893 --> 00:26:39.441
Uh-huh.

409
00:26:39.571 --> 00:26:43.003
Zeus. The big guy. He's your daddy.

410
00:26:43.086 --> 00:26:44.797
Mr Lightning Bolts!

411
00:26:44.883 --> 00:26:46.878
Read me a book, would ya, Da-da?

412
00:26:46.961 --> 00:26:49.870
- Zeus!
- "Once upon a time..."

413
00:26:49.956 --> 00:26:51.068
It's the truth!

414
00:26:51.155 --> 00:26:52.626
Please!

415
00:26:54.989 --> 00:26:57.540
<i>So you wanna be a hero, kid</i>

416
00:26:57.625 --> 00:26:59.052
<i>Well, whoop-de-do</i>

417
00:26:59.942 --> 00:27:02.252
<i>I have been around the block before</i>

418
00:27:02.339 --> 00:27:04.650
<i>With blockheads just like you</i>

419
00:27:04.736 --> 00:27:06.882
<i>Each and every one a disappointment</i>

420
00:27:06.973 --> 00:27:10.405
<i>Pain for which there ain't no ointment</i>

421
00:27:10.488 --> 00:27:13.876
<i>So much for excuses
Though a kid of "Zeus" is</i>

422
00:27:13.964 --> 00:27:17.069
<i>Askin' me to jump into the fray</i>

423
00:27:17.159 --> 00:27:19.949
<i>My answer is two words</i>

424
00:27:22.710 --> 00:27:24.182
Okay.

425
00:27:24.269 --> 00:27:26.340
- You mean you'll do it?
- You win.

426
00:27:26.426 --> 00:27:28.616
- You won't be sorry, Phil.
- Oh, gods.

427
00:27:28.703 --> 00:27:30.250
So when do we start?
Can we start now?

428
00:27:30.340 --> 00:27:31.330
<i>Oy vey.</i>

429
00:27:32.578 --> 00:27:37.241
<i>I'd given up hope
that someone would come along</i>

430
00:27:37.331 --> 00:27:42.082
<i>A fella who'd ring the bell for once
Not the gong</i>

431
00:27:42.164 --> 00:27:44.355
<i>The kind who wins trophies</i>

432
00:27:44.442 --> 00:27:46.272
<i>Won't settle for low fees</i>

433
00:27:46.358 --> 00:27:48.549
<i>At least semipro fees</i>

434
00:27:48.635 --> 00:27:51.425
<i>But, no, I get the greenhorn</i>

435
00:27:51.512 --> 00:27:55.782
<i>I've been out to pasture, pal
My ambition gone</i>

436
00:27:55.865 --> 00:28:00.376
<i>Content to spend lazy days
and to graze my lawn</i>

437
00:28:00.459 --> 00:28:02.769
<i>But you need an adviser</i>

438
00:28:02.855 --> 00:28:05.046
<i>A satyr, but wiser</i>

439
00:28:05.132 --> 00:28:07.681
<i>A good merchandiser and... Whoa</i>

440
00:28:08.207 --> 00:28:09.843
<i>There goes my ulcer</i>

441
00:28:09.925 --> 00:28:14.393
<i>I'm down to one last hope
and I hope it's you</i>

442
00:28:14.479 --> 00:28:18.827
<i>Though, kid, you're not exactly
a dream come true</i>

443
00:28:19.113 --> 00:28:23.417
<i>I trained enough turkeys
Who never came through</i>

444
00:28:23.506 --> 00:28:26.851
<i>You're my one last hope
So you'll have to do</i>

445
00:28:27.181 --> 00:28:28.533
Rule number six.

446
00:28:28.620 --> 00:28:30.734
When rescuing a damsel...

447
00:28:30.817 --> 00:28:32.811
...always handle with care.

448
00:28:34.731 --> 00:28:36.366
No!

449
00:28:37.688 --> 00:28:40.433
Rule number 95, kid. Concentrate!

450
00:28:42.440 --> 00:28:44.195
Rule number 96.

451
00:28:44.597 --> 00:28:45.948
Aim!

452
00:28:46.835 --> 00:28:51.379
<i>Demigods have faced the odds
And ended up a mockery</i>

453
00:28:51.468 --> 00:28:56.100
<i>Don't believe the stories
That you read on all the crockery</i>

454
00:28:56.182 --> 00:29:00.649
<i>To be a true hero, kid, is a dying art</i>

455
00:29:00.734 --> 00:29:02.968
<i>Like paintin' a masterpiece</i>

456
00:29:03.052 --> 00:29:05.287
<i>It's a work of heart</i>

457
00:29:05.370 --> 00:29:07.603
<i>It takes more than sinew</i>

458
00:29:07.686 --> 00:29:09.919
<i>Comes down to what's in you</i>

459
00:29:10.003 --> 00:29:13.467
<i>You have to continue to grow</i>

460
00:29:13.557 --> 00:29:15.748
Now, that's more like it!

461
00:29:15.834 --> 00:29:21.064
<i>I'm down to one last shot
And my last high note</i>

462
00:29:21.866 --> 00:29:26.617
<i>Before that blasted underworld
gets my goat</i>

463
00:29:26.699 --> 00:29:28.770
<i>My dreams are on you, kid</i>

464
00:29:28.856 --> 00:29:30.970
<i>Go make 'em come true</i>

465
00:29:31.053 --> 00:29:32.927
<i>Climb that uphill slope</i>

466
00:29:33.011 --> 00:29:35.278
<i>Keep pushin' that envelope</i>

467
00:29:35.368 --> 00:29:37.002
<i>You're my one last hope</i>

468
00:29:37.084 --> 00:29:42.588
<i>And, kid, it's up to you</i>

469
00:29:44.236 --> 00:29:45.662
Yeah!

470
00:29:47.830 --> 00:29:49.976
Did you see that?

471
00:29:50.066 --> 00:29:52.660
Next stop, Olympus.

472
00:29:53.303 --> 00:29:55.254
All right, just take it easy, champ.

473
00:29:55.340 --> 00:29:57.486
I am ready. I want to get off this island.

474
00:29:57.576 --> 00:29:59.886
I want to see battles and monsters.

475
00:29:59.973 --> 00:30:01.728
Rescue some damsels.

476
00:30:01.810 --> 00:30:03.804
You know, heroic stuff.

477
00:30:04.247 --> 00:30:07.277
- Well...
- Aw, come on! Phil!

478
00:30:07.363 --> 00:30:10.632
Well, okay. Okay, you want a road test?
Saddle up, kid.

479
00:30:10.718 --> 00:30:12.951
We're going to Thebes!

480
00:30:14.034 --> 00:30:16.704
- So what's in Thebes?
- A lot of problems.

481
00:30:16.790 --> 00:30:20.178
It's a big, tough town.
Good place to start buildin' a rep.

482
00:30:22.183 --> 00:30:26.290
Sounds like your basic DID,
Damsel in Distress.

483
00:30:32.928 --> 00:30:35.314
Not so fast, sweetheart.

484
00:30:35.404 --> 00:30:37.758
I swear, Nessus. Put me down or I'll...

485
00:30:37.840 --> 00:30:40.347
Whoo! I like 'em fiery!

486
00:30:40.797 --> 00:30:42.464
Now, remember, kid.

487
00:30:42.554 --> 00:30:44.384
First, analyze the situation.

488
00:30:44.472 --> 00:30:46.618
Don't just barrel in there
without thinking.

489
00:30:48.466 --> 00:30:50.820
He's losin' points for this!

490
00:30:51.022 --> 00:30:52.896
- You don't know what you're...
- Halt!

491
00:30:55.776 --> 00:30:58.446
Step aside, two legs.

492
00:30:58.532 --> 00:31:02.204
Pardon me, my good sir.

493
00:31:02.287 --> 00:31:03.972
I'll have to ask you to
release that young...

494
00:31:04.044 --> 00:31:06.878
- Keep movin', junior.
- Lady.

495
00:31:06.961 --> 00:31:10.306
But you...
Aren't you a damsel in distress?

496
00:31:10.395 --> 00:31:13.348
I'm a damsel, I'm in distress.

497
00:31:13.432 --> 00:31:16.297
I can handle this. Have a nice day.

498
00:31:16.428 --> 00:31:18.018
Uh.

499
00:31:18.145 --> 00:31:20.771
Ma'am, I'm afraid you may be
too close to the situation to realize...

500
00:31:22.898 --> 00:31:23.889
Ohhh!

501
00:31:24.337 --> 00:31:27.485
- What are you doin'? Get your sword!
- Sword. Right, right.

502
00:31:27.572 --> 00:31:30.601
Rule number 15,
a hero is only as good as his weapon!

503
00:31:38.277 --> 00:31:41.263
Whoa! Hold it! Hold on!
He's gotta do it on his own.

504
00:31:41.512 --> 00:31:44.422
Come on, kid! Concentrate!

505
00:31:44.509 --> 00:31:46.415
Use your head!

506
00:31:47.105 --> 00:31:48.172
Oh.

507
00:31:53.456 --> 00:31:56.125
All right! Not bad, kid!

508
00:31:56.212 --> 00:31:58.957
Not exactly what I had in mind,
but not bad.

509
00:32:01.125 --> 00:32:05.636
Oh, gee, miss, I'm really sorry.
That was dumb.

510
00:32:06.038 --> 00:32:07.748
Yeah.

511
00:32:08.755 --> 00:32:10.063
Excuse me.

512
00:32:14.986 --> 00:32:18.451
<i>Nice work! Excelente!</i>

513
00:32:18.540 --> 00:32:20.535
Is Wonderboy here for real?

514
00:32:20.618 --> 00:32:23.364
What are you talkin' about?
Of course he's real.

515
00:32:23.454 --> 00:32:24.412
Whoa!

516
00:32:25.371 --> 00:32:29.883
And by the way, sweet cheeks,
I'm real, too.

517
00:32:30.045 --> 00:32:31.636
Ugh!

518
00:32:32.202 --> 00:32:34.468
Yee-hah! Yahoo!

519
00:32:40.271 --> 00:32:41.228
Whoa!

520
00:33:07.474 --> 00:33:09.468
- How was that, Phil?
- Rein it in, rookie.

521
00:33:09.551 --> 00:33:12.263
You can get away with mistakes
like those in the minor decathlons,

522
00:33:12.346 --> 00:33:14.853
but this is the big leagues!

523
00:33:14.943 --> 00:33:16.774
At least I beat him, didn't I?

524
00:33:16.860 --> 00:33:20.489
Next time, don't let your guard down
because of a pair of big goo-goo eyes!

525
00:33:21.094 --> 00:33:25.127
It's like I keep tellin' ya.
You gotta stay focused, and... You...

526
00:33:34.716 --> 00:33:37.701
Are you all right, Miss...

527
00:33:37.791 --> 00:33:41.495
Megara. My friends call me Meg.
At least, they would if I had any friends.

528
00:33:41.586 --> 00:33:46.054
So did they give you a name
along with all those rippling pectorals?

529
00:33:46.139 --> 00:33:48.646
Uh, I'm, um, uh...

530
00:33:50.893 --> 00:33:52.441
Are you always this articulate?

531
00:33:52.532 --> 00:33:55.441
Hercules. My...
My name is Hercules.

532
00:33:55.966 --> 00:33:58.832
Hercules. I think I prefer Wonderboy.

533
00:33:59.641 --> 00:34:03.706
So, how'd you get mixed up with the...

534
00:34:03.796 --> 00:34:06.150
Pinhead with hooves?
Well, you know how men are.

535
00:34:06.232 --> 00:34:09.817
They think that "No" means "Yes," and
"Get lost" means "Take me, I'm yours."

536
00:34:12.223 --> 00:34:14.698
Don't worry.
Shorty here can explain it to ya later.

537
00:34:15.819 --> 00:34:20.450
Well, thanks for everything, Herc.
It's been a real slice.

538
00:34:20.932 --> 00:34:24.157
Wait! Can we give you a ride?

539
00:34:27.801 --> 00:34:30.547
I don't think
your pinto likes me very much.

540
00:34:30.639 --> 00:34:35.390
Pegasus? Oh, no. Don't be silly.
He'd be more than happy to... Ow.

541
00:34:37.388 --> 00:34:42.934
I'll be all right. I'm a big, tough girl.
I tie my own sandals and everything.

542
00:34:44.459 --> 00:34:46.410
Bye-bye, Wonderboy.

543
00:34:46.816 --> 00:34:48.242
Bye.

544
00:34:49.332 --> 00:34:52.601
She's something. Isn't she, Phil?

545
00:34:52.687 --> 00:34:55.281
Yeah. Yeah. She's really something.

546
00:34:55.364 --> 00:34:56.758
A real pain in the patella!

547
00:34:56.842 --> 00:34:59.915
Earth to Herc!
Come in, Herc! Come in, Herc!

548
00:34:59.997 --> 00:35:02.710
We got a job to do, remember?

549
00:35:02.794 --> 00:35:04.460
Thebes is still waitin'.

550
00:35:04.551 --> 00:35:07.297
Yeah. Yeah. I know.

551
00:35:17.653 --> 00:35:19.679
Aw... How cute.

552
00:35:19.770 --> 00:35:22.277
A couple of rodents
looking for a theme park.

553
00:35:22.366 --> 00:35:25.679
Who you callin' a rodent, sister?
I'm a bunny!

554
00:35:25.762 --> 00:35:27.113
And I'm his gopher.

555
00:35:27.240 --> 00:35:28.197
Ta-da!

556
00:35:28.877 --> 00:35:30.631
I thought I smelled a rat.

557
00:35:30.714 --> 00:35:32.350
Meg?

558
00:35:32.432 --> 00:35:34.187
Speak of the devil.

559
00:35:34.270 --> 00:35:38.183
Meg, my little flower, my little bird,
my little nut, Meg.

560
00:35:38.265 --> 00:35:40.138
What exactly happened here?

561
00:35:40.221 --> 00:35:42.175
I thought you were gonna
persuade the river guardian

562
00:35:42.219 --> 00:35:43.734
to join my team for the uprising,

563
00:35:43.817 --> 00:35:46.487
and here I am,
kind of river guardian-less.

564
00:35:46.573 --> 00:35:50.441
I gave it my best shot,
but he made me an offer I had to refuse.

565
00:35:50.526 --> 00:35:53.034
Fine. So, instead of subtracting
two years from your sentence,

566
00:35:53.124 --> 00:35:54.791
hey, I'm gonna add two on, okay?

567
00:35:54.881 --> 00:35:55.917
Give that your best shot.

568
00:35:56.000 --> 00:35:58.909
It wasn't my fault.
It was this wonderboy, Hercules.

569
00:35:59.715 --> 00:36:03.344
Hercules?
Why does that name ring a bell?

570
00:36:03.430 --> 00:36:06.142
I don't know.
Maybe we owe him money?

571
00:36:06.226 --> 00:36:10.617
- What was that name again?
- Hercules.

572
00:36:10.700 --> 00:36:12.693
He comes on with
this big, innocent farm boy routine,

573
00:36:12.777 --> 00:36:14.472
but I could see through that
in a Peloponnesian minute.

574
00:36:14.494 --> 00:36:15.452
Wait a minute.

575
00:36:15.493 --> 00:36:18.565
Wasn't Hercules the name
of that kid we were supposed to...

576
00:36:18.648 --> 00:36:20.600
- Oh, my gods!
- Oh, my gods!

577
00:36:20.686 --> 00:36:21.993
Run for it!

578
00:36:22.084 --> 00:36:25.157
So you took care of him, huh?

579
00:36:25.239 --> 00:36:27.146
Dead as a door nail.

580
00:36:27.236 --> 00:36:29.950
Weren't those your exact words?

581
00:36:30.033 --> 00:36:31.820
This might be a different Hercules.

582
00:36:31.911 --> 00:36:35.418
Yeah! I mean, Hercules
is a very popular name nowadays!

583
00:36:35.505 --> 00:36:38.732
Remember, like, a few years ago,
every other boy was named Jason,

584
00:36:38.821 --> 00:36:40.456
and the girls were all named Brittany?

585
00:36:40.538 --> 00:36:44.886
I'm about to rearrange the cosmos,

586
00:36:44.972 --> 00:36:51.640
and the one schlemiel who can louse
it up is waltzing around in the woods!

587
00:36:55.597 --> 00:36:57.428
Wait. Wait, big guy.

588
00:36:57.515 --> 00:36:59.782
- We can still cut in on his waltzing.
- That's right!

589
00:36:59.871 --> 00:37:02.901
And at least we made him mortal.
That's a good thing.

590
00:37:02.987 --> 00:37:04.534
Didn't we?

591
00:37:04.744 --> 00:37:05.812
Hmm.

592
00:37:06.423 --> 00:37:07.893
Fortunately for the three of you,

593
00:37:07.981 --> 00:37:11.652
we still have time to correct
this rather egregious oversight.

594
00:37:11.734 --> 00:37:15.048
And this time, no foul-ups.

595
00:37:17.847 --> 00:37:18.804
Wow!

596
00:37:20.643 --> 00:37:23.956
- Is that all one town?
- One town, a million troubles.

597
00:37:24.038 --> 00:37:28.102
The one and only Thebes.
The Big Olive itself.

598
00:37:28.192 --> 00:37:31.265
If you can make it there,
you can make it anywhere.

599
00:37:38.258 --> 00:37:42.171
Stick with me, kid.
This city is a dangerous place.

600
00:37:42.252 --> 00:37:46.078
- Look where you're goin', numbskull!
- Hey, I'm walkin' here!

601
00:37:46.167 --> 00:37:48.641
You see what I mean?
I'm tellin' you, wackos.

602
00:37:48.724 --> 00:37:51.917
Pitta bread. Pitta bread.
Get your pitta bread here.

603
00:37:51.999 --> 00:37:53.514
Hey, Mack.

604
00:37:53.597 --> 00:37:54.633
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

605
00:37:54.875 --> 00:37:57.740
- You wanna buy a sundial?
- He's not interested, all right?

606
00:37:57.832 --> 00:37:58.822
Come on, kid.

607
00:37:58.909 --> 00:38:01.896
The end is coming! Can't you feel it?

608
00:38:01.986 --> 00:38:06.049
Yes, yes. Thank you for the info. Yes.
We'll ponder that for a while.

609
00:38:06.140 --> 00:38:07.434
Just stare at the sidewalk. Come on.

610
00:38:07.457 --> 00:38:09.811
Don't make eye contact.
People here are nuts.

611
00:38:09.895 --> 00:38:11.966
That's because
they live in a city of turmoil.

612
00:38:12.052 --> 00:38:13.043
Trust me, kid.

613
00:38:13.130 --> 00:38:15.320
You're gonna be
just what the doctor ordered.

614
00:38:16.285 --> 00:38:20.393
It was tragic!
We lost everything in the fire.

615
00:38:20.479 --> 00:38:23.389
Everything except old Snowball here.

616
00:38:24.554 --> 00:38:27.299
Now, were the fires
before or after the earthquake?

617
00:38:27.390 --> 00:38:29.461
They were after the earthquake.
I remember.

618
00:38:29.547 --> 00:38:30.899
But before the flood.

619
00:38:30.986 --> 00:38:34.254
Don't even get me started
on the crime rate.

620
00:38:34.340 --> 00:38:37.773
Thebes has certainly
gone downhill in a hurry.

621
00:38:37.855 --> 00:38:39.370
Tell me about it.

622
00:38:39.454 --> 00:38:41.404
It seems like every time I turn around,

623
00:38:41.491 --> 00:38:43.681
there's some new monster
wreaking havoc and I...

624
00:38:43.767 --> 00:38:47.200
All we need now is a plague of locusts.

625
00:38:48.921 --> 00:38:51.994
That's it! I'm movin' to Sparta!

626
00:38:52.076 --> 00:38:53.263
Excuse me.

627
00:38:54.352 --> 00:38:56.260
It, uh...

628
00:38:56.350 --> 00:38:59.738
...seems to me that what
you folks need is a hero.

629
00:39:01.064 --> 00:39:02.893
Yeah, and who are you?

630
00:39:04.858 --> 00:39:09.326
I'm Hercules, and I happen to be a hero.

631
00:39:10.610 --> 00:39:12.877
- Is that so?
- A hero!

632
00:39:12.966 --> 00:39:17.315
- Have you ever saved a town before?
- Uh, no. Not exactly, but I...

633
00:39:17.401 --> 00:39:19.787
Have you ever
reversed a natural disaster?

634
00:39:19.878 --> 00:39:22.187
Well, uh, no.

635
00:39:22.274 --> 00:39:25.261
Listen to this.
He's just another chariot chaser.

636
00:39:25.350 --> 00:39:27.421
- This we need.
- That's a laugh.

637
00:39:27.507 --> 00:39:29.740
- Don't you pea brains get it?
- Hmm?

638
00:39:29.863 --> 00:39:32.010
This kid is the genuine article.

639
00:39:32.219 --> 00:39:35.925
Hey, isn't that the goat-man
who trained Achilles?

640
00:39:36.015 --> 00:39:37.606
Watch it, pal.

641
00:39:37.693 --> 00:39:39.839
Yeah, you're right.

642
00:39:39.929 --> 00:39:42.316
Hey, nice job on those heels!

643
00:39:42.406 --> 00:39:44.880
Ya missed a spot!

644
00:39:44.963 --> 00:39:46.869
I got your heel right here!

645
00:39:46.960 --> 00:39:48.986
I'll wipe that stupid grin
off your face! You...

646
00:39:49.076 --> 00:39:52.226
Hey, Phil! Phil! Phil! Take it easy. Phil.

647
00:39:52.313 --> 00:39:54.700
What are you, crazy? Sheesh!

648
00:39:54.869 --> 00:40:00.012
Young man, we need
a professional hero, not an amateur.

649
00:40:01.381 --> 00:40:03.407
Well, wait. Stop!

650
00:40:08.490 --> 00:40:12.195
How am I supposed to prove myself
a hero if nobody will give me a chance?

651
00:40:12.285 --> 00:40:13.353
You'll get your chance.

652
00:40:13.443 --> 00:40:16.308
You just need some kind of
catastrophe or disaster.

653
00:40:16.399 --> 00:40:18.034
Please.

654
00:40:18.156 --> 00:40:21.230
Help! Please!
There's been a terrible accident!

655
00:40:21.313 --> 00:40:23.383
- Meg?
- Speakin' of disasters.

656
00:40:23.789 --> 00:40:26.938
Wonderboy! Hercules!
Thank goodness!

657
00:40:27.024 --> 00:40:28.418
What's wrong?

658
00:40:28.502 --> 00:40:31.696
Outside of town, two little boys.
They were playing in the gorge.

659
00:40:31.778 --> 00:40:34.328
There was this terrible rockslide.

660
00:40:34.414 --> 00:40:37.040
- They're trapped!
- Kids? Trapped?

661
00:40:37.130 --> 00:40:38.646
Phil, this is great!

662
00:40:38.729 --> 00:40:40.453
You're really choked up about this,
aren't ya?

663
00:40:40.526 --> 00:40:41.484
Come on!

664
00:40:41.524 --> 00:40:46.068
No, I... You don't...
I have this terrible fear of heights!

665
00:40:50.711 --> 00:40:53.381
I'm right behind ya, kid! Whoo!

666
00:40:53.468 --> 00:40:55.298
I'm way behind ya, kid.

667
00:40:55.384 --> 00:40:57.531
I got a fur wedgie.

668
00:41:04.292 --> 00:41:06.003
- Are you okay?
- I'll be fine.

669
00:41:06.090 --> 00:41:08.205
Just get me down
before I ruin the upholstery.

670
00:41:08.288 --> 00:41:11.197
- Help! I can't breathe!
- Hurry!

671
00:41:11.283 --> 00:41:13.637
- Get us out!
- We're suffocating!

672
00:41:14.718 --> 00:41:17.824
Somebody call IX-I-I!

673
00:41:17.914 --> 00:41:19.462
Easy, fellas. You'll be all right.

674
00:41:19.552 --> 00:41:23.856
- We can't last much longer!
- Get us out before we get crushed!

675
00:41:41.920 --> 00:41:44.034
- How you boys doin'?
- We're okay now.

676
00:41:44.117 --> 00:41:47.582
Jeepers, mister. You're really strong.

677
00:41:47.672 --> 00:41:51.018
Well, try to be a little more careful
next time, okay, kids?

678
00:41:51.107 --> 00:41:52.698
We sure will.

679
00:41:57.938 --> 00:41:59.812
A stirring performance, boys.

680
00:41:59.896 --> 00:42:01.651
I was really moved.

681
00:42:02.892 --> 00:42:05.081
"Jeepers, mister"?

682
00:42:05.168 --> 00:42:08.242
I was going for innocence.

683
00:42:08.324 --> 00:42:12.357
And, hey, two thumbs
way, way up for our leading lady.

684
00:42:12.439 --> 00:42:14.074
What a dish. What a doll.

685
00:42:14.156 --> 00:42:16.749
Get outta there, you big lug,
white you still can.

686
00:42:17.072 --> 00:42:19.142
Phil, I did great.

687
00:42:19.468 --> 00:42:21.463
They even applauded, sort of.

688
00:42:21.826 --> 00:42:23.416
Huh!

689
00:42:23.504 --> 00:42:26.935
I hate to burst your bubble, kid,
but that ain't applause.

690
00:42:34.088 --> 00:42:36.758
Phil? What do you call that thing?

691
00:42:36.844 --> 00:42:37.999
Two words.

692
00:42:39.321 --> 00:42:41.031
Am-scray!

693
00:42:43.795 --> 00:42:47.980
Let's get ready to rumble!

694
00:42:53.941 --> 00:42:56.447
That's it. Dance around! Dance around!

695
00:42:56.537 --> 00:42:59.524
Watch the teeth. Watch the teeth.
Keep going. Come on. Come on.

696
00:42:59.613 --> 00:43:02.925
Lead with your left.
Lead with your left! Your other left!

697
00:43:27.774 --> 00:43:30.281
Whoa!

698
00:43:54.497 --> 00:43:57.809
All right! All right! You're bad! Okay!

699
00:43:57.892 --> 00:44:01.402
See, Phil? That... That wasn't so hard.

700
00:44:01.488 --> 00:44:03.122
Kid, kid, kid.

701
00:44:03.205 --> 00:44:04.632
How many horns do ya see?

702
00:44:04.723 --> 00:44:06.390
Six?

703
00:44:06.480 --> 00:44:09.226
Eh, close enough.
Let's get you cleaned up.

704
00:44:13.151 --> 00:44:16.017
Guys, guys, relax.

705
00:44:16.107 --> 00:44:17.894
It's only half-time.

706
00:44:20.901 --> 00:44:22.776
That doesn't sound good.

707
00:44:30.088 --> 00:44:31.636
Definitely not good!

708
00:44:42.351 --> 00:44:43.342
Whoa! Whoa!

709
00:44:59.248 --> 00:45:02.038
Will you forget the head-slicing thing?

710
00:45:02.203 --> 00:45:03.239
Hyah!

711
00:45:09.313 --> 00:45:12.746
Phil, I don't think we covered
this one in basic training!

712
00:45:23.533 --> 00:45:26.083
My favorite part of the game,

713
00:45:29.125 --> 00:45:30.879
Sudden death.

714
00:45:37.275 --> 00:45:38.232
Huh?

715
00:45:51.016 --> 00:45:52.170
Oh!

716
00:45:52.853 --> 00:45:56.557
There goes another one.
Just like Achilles.

717
00:45:59.044 --> 00:46:00.831
Game.

718
00:46:00.921 --> 00:46:02.676
Set.

719
00:46:02.759 --> 00:46:04.067
Match.

720
00:46:26.846 --> 00:46:31.717
Phil, you gotta admit.
That was pretty heroic.

721
00:46:31.800 --> 00:46:36.147
Ya did it, kid! Ya did it!
You won by a landslide!

722
00:46:38.670 --> 00:46:40.664
Hades mad.

723
00:46:43.263 --> 00:46:45.933
Well, what do ya know?

724
00:46:49.814 --> 00:46:53.606
From that day forward,
our boy Hercules could do no wrong.

725
00:46:53.689 --> 00:46:56.957
He was so hot, steam looked cool.

726
00:46:57.044 --> 00:46:59.190
<i>Oh, yeah</i>

727
00:47:00.120 --> 00:47:02.952
<i>Bless my soul
Herc was on a roll</i>

728
00:47:03.035 --> 00:47:05.868
<i>Person of the week
in every Greek opinion poll</i>

729
00:47:05.950 --> 00:47:08.458
<i>- What a pro
- Herc could stop a show</i>

730
00:47:08.548 --> 00:47:11.413
<i>Point him at a monster
and you're talkin' SRO</i>

731
00:47:11.504 --> 00:47:14.174
<i>- He was a no one
- A zero, zero</i>

732
00:47:14.261 --> 00:47:16.974
<i>- Now he's a honcho
- He's a hero</i>

733
00:47:17.096 --> 00:47:19.766
<i>Here was a kid with his act down pat</i>

734
00:47:19.852 --> 00:47:22.598
<i>Zero to hero in no time flat</i>

735
00:47:22.688 --> 00:47:25.359
<i>- Zero to hero
- Just like that</i>

736
00:47:25.445 --> 00:47:27.831
<i>When he smiled the girls went wild</i>

737
00:47:27.962 --> 00:47:30.631
