<i>Oh</i>

972
01:00:26.243 --> 01:00:29.556
<i>At least out loud</i>

973
01:00:29.638 --> 01:00:32.352
<i>I won't say I'm in</i>

974
01:00:33.193 --> 01:00:36.658
<i>- Love
- Shoo-doo, shoo-doo</i>

975
01:00:36.828 --> 01:00:39.215
<i>Sha-la-la-la-Ia-la-la-la</i>

976
01:00:39.504 --> 01:00:40.780
<i>Ah</i>

977
01:00:50.889 --> 01:00:53.319
Hey, what's the buzz, huh, Meg?

978
01:00:53.405 --> 01:00:56.674
What is the weak link
in Wonderboy's chain?

979
01:00:56.761 --> 01:00:58.951
Get yourself another girl. I'm through.

980
01:00:59.037 --> 01:01:00.812
I'm sorry. Do you mind
runnin' that by me again?

981
01:01:00.834 --> 01:01:03.384
I must have had a chunk of brimstone
wedged in my ear or something.

982
01:01:03.471 --> 01:01:07.416
Then read my lips! Forget it.

983
01:01:07.506 --> 01:01:11.810
Meg, Meg, Meg,
my sweet, deluded little minion.

984
01:01:11.900 --> 01:01:16.487
Aren't we forgetting one teensy-weensy,
but ever so crucial little, tiny detail?

985
01:01:16.573 --> 01:01:18.447
I own you!

986
01:01:20.369 --> 01:01:22.961
- I got another horn here.
- You work for me.

987
01:01:23.044 --> 01:01:25.310
That kid's gonna be
doin' laps for a month.

988
01:01:25.401 --> 01:01:28.507
If I say, "Sing," you say,
"Hey, name that tune."

989
01:01:28.598 --> 01:01:32.901
If I say, "I want Wonderboy's head
on a platter," you say...

990
01:01:33.030 --> 01:01:34.817
Medium or well-done.

991
01:01:34.908 --> 01:01:39.300
Oh! I knew that dame was trouble.
This is gonna break the kid's heart.

992
01:01:39.461 --> 01:01:42.413
- I'll work on that.
- I'm sorry. You hear that sound?

993
01:01:42.497 --> 01:01:46.606
That's the sound of your freedom
fluttering out the window forever.

994
01:01:46.691 --> 01:01:49.917
I don't care.
I'm not gonna help you hurt him.

995
01:01:50.965 --> 01:01:54.791
I can't believe you're
getting so worked up about some guy.

996
01:01:54.881 --> 01:01:57.027
This one is different.
He's honest, and he's sweet...

997
01:01:57.117 --> 01:01:58.074
Please!

998
01:01:58.156 --> 01:01:59.891
- He would never do anything to hurt me.
- He's a guy!

999
01:01:59.913 --> 01:02:03.945
Besides, O oneness,
you can't beat him.

1000
01:02:04.028 --> 01:02:07.656
He has no weaknesses. He's gonna...

1001
01:02:08.061 --> 01:02:11.645
I think he does, Meg.

1002
01:02:11.737 --> 01:02:14.930
I truly think he does.

1003
01:02:25.877 --> 01:02:26.944
Ha ha!

1004
01:02:30.270 --> 01:02:31.546
Whoo-hoo!

1005
01:02:37.061 --> 01:02:39.328
Hey, Phil! What happened to you?

1006
01:02:39.417 --> 01:02:40.770
Kid, we gotta talk.

1007
01:02:40.857 --> 01:02:44.365
Phil, I just had
the greatest day of my life!

1008
01:02:44.451 --> 01:02:46.685
I can't stop thinking about Meg.

1009
01:02:46.848 --> 01:02:48.961
She's something else.

1010
01:02:49.125 --> 01:02:52.232
Kid, I'm tr yin' to talk to ya!
Will you come down here and listen?

1011
01:02:52.320 --> 01:02:56.952
Aw, how can I come down there
when I'm feeling so up?

1012
01:03:21.161 --> 01:03:22.588
Gotcha!

1013
01:03:22.679 --> 01:03:24.912
Ah, very nice!
What I'm tr yin' to say is...

1014
01:03:24.995 --> 01:03:27.426
That if it wasn't for you,
I never would have met her.

1015
01:03:27.511 --> 01:03:29.266
Oh, I owe ya big time.

1016
01:03:29.350 --> 01:03:31.083
Will you just knock it off
for a couple of seconds?

1017
01:03:31.107 --> 01:03:33.613
Rule number 38. Come on, Phil.
Keep them up there, huh?

1018
01:03:33.702 --> 01:03:36.656
- Phil, I got two words for ya, duck!
- Listen to me! She's...

1019
01:03:36.740 --> 01:03:38.090
- A dream come true?
- Not exactly.

1020
01:03:38.176 --> 01:03:40.203
- More beautiful than Aphrodite?
- Aside from that!

1021
01:03:40.294 --> 01:03:44.325
- The most wonderful...
- She's a fraud!

1022
01:03:44.408 --> 01:03:46.882
She's been playin' ya for a sap!

1023
01:03:46.965 --> 01:03:49.874
- Aw, come on. Stop kiddin' around.
- I'm not kiddin' around.

1024
01:03:49.960 --> 01:03:51.655
I know you're upset about today,
but that's no reason to...

1025
01:03:51.678 --> 01:03:52.734
Kid, you're missin' the point.

1026
01:03:52.757 --> 01:03:55.067
- The point is, I love her.
- She don't love you.

1027
01:03:55.153 --> 01:03:57.267
- You're crazy.
- She's nothin' but a two-timin'...

1028
01:03:57.350 --> 01:03:59.344
- Stop it!
- No-good, lyin', schemin'...

1029
01:03:59.427 --> 01:04:00.702
Shut up!

1030
01:04:03.903 --> 01:04:05.657
Phil. I...

1031
01:04:06.657 --> 01:04:07.648
I'm sorry.

1032
01:04:07.737 --> 01:04:11.484
Okay, okay, that's it.
You won't face the truth? Fine.

1033
01:04:11.571 --> 01:04:13.958
Phil, wait. Where you going?

1034
01:04:14.087 --> 01:04:17.399
I'm hoppin' the first barge out of here.
I'm goin' home.

1035
01:04:18.122 --> 01:04:20.116
Fine!

1036
01:04:20.199 --> 01:04:23.065
Go! I don't... I don't need you.

1037
01:04:25.351 --> 01:04:28.458
I thought you were gonna be
the all-time champ,

1038
01:04:28.547 --> 01:04:30.934
not the all-time chump.

1039
01:04:33.701 --> 01:04:36.326
Geez Louise!
What got his goat, huh?

1040
01:04:39.053 --> 01:04:41.080
Baboom. Name is Hades,
Lord of the Dead.

1041
01:04:41.170 --> 01:04:43.120
- Hi. How ya doin'?
- Not now, okay?

1042
01:04:43.208 --> 01:04:45.813
Hey, hey. I only need a few seconds
and I'm a fast talker, all right?

1043
01:04:45.843 --> 01:04:48.601
I've got the major deal in the works.
A real estate venture, if you will.

1044
01:04:48.639 --> 01:04:50.634
And Herc, you little devil you.
May I call you Herc?

1045
01:04:50.717 --> 01:04:52.863
You seem to be constantly
getting in the way of it.

1046
01:04:52.953 --> 01:04:54.108
You've got the wrong guy.

1047
01:04:54.191 --> 01:04:57.536
Hear me out, ya little...
Just hear me out, okay?

1048
01:04:57.627 --> 01:04:59.578
So I would be eternally grateful

1049
01:04:59.664 --> 01:05:02.616
if you would just take a day off
from this hero business of yours.

1050
01:05:02.700 --> 01:05:05.686
I mean, monsters, natural disasters.
You wait a day, okay?

1051
01:05:05.775 --> 01:05:07.951
- You're out of your mind.
- Not so fast, because, ya see,

1052
01:05:07.974 --> 01:05:11.199
I do have a little leverage
you might wanna know about.

1053
01:05:11.967 --> 01:05:13.918
- Meg!
- Don't listen, Herc...

1054
01:05:16.361 --> 01:05:18.269
- Let her go!
- Here's the trade-off.

1055
01:05:18.359 --> 01:05:21.311
You give up your strength
for about 24 hours, okay?

1056
01:05:21.394 --> 01:05:23.301
Say the next 24 hours.

1057
01:05:23.391 --> 01:05:25.341
And Meg here is free as a bird
and safe from harm.

1058
01:05:25.428 --> 01:05:27.563
We dance, we kiss, we schmooze,
we carry on, we go home happy.

1059
01:05:27.586 --> 01:05:28.938
What d'ya say? Come on.

1060
01:05:30.022 --> 01:05:31.929
People are gonna get hurt, aren't they?

1061
01:05:32.019 --> 01:05:35.407
Nah! I mean, it's a possibility.
It happens 'cause, you know, it's war.

1062
01:05:35.494 --> 01:05:37.968
But what can I tell ya? Anyway,
what do you owe these people?

1063
01:05:38.051 --> 01:05:40.764
Isn't Meg, little smoochy face,
isn't she more important than they are?

1064
01:05:40.847 --> 01:05:42.798
- Stop it!
- Isn't she?

1065
01:05:42.884 --> 01:05:45.435
You've gotta swear
she'll be safe from any harm.

1066
01:05:45.522 --> 01:05:47.351
Fine, okay. I'll give you that one.

1067
01:05:47.438 --> 01:05:50.271
Meg is safe, otherwise you get your
strength right back. Yadda yadda.

1068
01:05:50.353 --> 01:05:53.502
Fine print. Boilerplate. Okay? Done.
What d'ya say we shake on it?

1069
01:05:53.589 --> 01:05:55.824
Hey, I really don't have, like,
time to bat this around.

1070
01:05:55.907 --> 01:05:57.681
I'm kind of on a schedule here.
I got plans for August. Okay?

1071
01:05:57.704 --> 01:06:00.690
I need an answer, like, now.
Going once, going twice...

1072
01:06:00.779 --> 01:06:03.733
- All right!
- Yes, we're there! Bam!

1073
01:06:11.245 --> 01:06:13.959
You may feel just a little queasy.
It's kinda natural.

1074
01:06:14.041 --> 01:06:15.871
Maybe you should sit down!

1075
01:06:17.995 --> 01:06:21.908
Now you know how it feels
to be just like everybody else.

1076
01:06:21.990 --> 01:06:24.823
Isn't it just peachy?

1077
01:06:25.586 --> 01:06:27.699
Oh!
You'll love this. One more thing.

1078
01:06:27.782 --> 01:06:32.131
Meg, babe, a deal's a deal.
You're off the hook.

1079
01:06:32.855 --> 01:06:35.841
And by the way, Herc,
is she not a fabulous little actress?

1080
01:06:35.932 --> 01:06:37.358
- Stop it.
- What do you mean?

1081
01:06:37.448 --> 01:06:41.361
I mean your little chickie-poo here
was working for me all the time.

1082
01:06:41.443 --> 01:06:42.401
Duh.

1083
01:06:42.482 --> 01:06:44.476
You're... You're lying!

1084
01:06:45.398 --> 01:06:49.985
- Help!
- Jeepers, mister, you're really strong.

1085
01:06:50.071 --> 01:06:52.545
Couldn't have done it without you,
sugar, sweetheart, babe.

1086
01:06:52.628 --> 01:06:53.902
No! It's not like that.

1087
01:06:53.986 --> 01:06:56.731
I didn't mean to... I couldn't... I...

1088
01:06:57.101 --> 01:06:58.889
I'm so sorry.

1089
01:06:58.979 --> 01:07:03.087
Our hero's a zero! Our hero's a zero!

1090
01:07:04.211 --> 01:07:05.965
Well, gotta blaze.

1091
01:07:06.049 --> 01:07:10.397
There's a whole cosmos up there
waiting for me with, hey, my name on it.

1092
01:07:12.680 --> 01:07:16.188
So much for the preliminaries,
and now on to the main event!

1093
01:07:28.697 --> 01:07:31.846
Brothers! Titans!

1094
01:07:31.933 --> 01:07:35.039
Look at you in your squalid prison!

1095
01:07:35.128 --> 01:07:38.081
Who put you down there?

1096
01:07:38.164 --> 01:07:40.191
Zeus!

1097
01:07:40.282 --> 01:07:46.472
And now that I set you free, what is
the first thing you are going to do?

1098
01:07:46.793 --> 01:07:50.018
- Destroy him!
- Good answer.

1099
01:07:52.304 --> 01:07:56.130
Crush Zeus!

1100
01:07:58.736 --> 01:08:01.809
Freeze him!

1101
01:08:06.047 --> 01:08:08.401
Melt Zeus!

1102
01:08:09.441 --> 01:08:14.106
Blow him away!

1103
01:08:16.511 --> 01:08:18.581
Zeus!

1104
01:08:20.785 --> 01:08:22.453
- Uh, guys?
- Huh?

1105
01:08:22.783 --> 01:08:24.613
Olympus would be that way.

1106
01:08:25.460 --> 01:08:28.652
- Zeus!
- Freeze him!

1107
01:08:29.453 --> 01:08:31.240
Hold it, bright eye.

1108
01:08:31.372 --> 01:08:34.236
I have a special job for you,
my optic friend.

1109
01:08:40.718 --> 01:08:42.232
Ah, huh?

1110
01:08:42.436 --> 01:08:45.062
Destroy Zeus!

1111
01:08:45.232 --> 01:08:48.304
Oh, we're in trouble!
Big trouble! I gotta...

1112
01:08:48.866 --> 01:08:51.177
My lord and lady,
the Titans have escaped,

1113
01:08:51.263 --> 01:08:53.169
and they're practically at our gates!

1114
01:08:53.261 --> 01:08:57.173
Sound the alarm!
Launch an immediate counterattack!

1115
01:08:57.255 --> 01:08:59.686
- Go! Go!
- Gone, babe.

1116
01:09:02.527 --> 01:09:03.563
Huh?

1117
01:09:08.639 --> 01:09:09.794
Charge!

1118
01:09:09.877 --> 01:09:10.835
Yah!

1119
01:09:10.917 --> 01:09:12.823
On to battle!

1120
01:09:18.626 --> 01:09:19.781
Eeyah!

1121
01:09:23.778 --> 01:09:25.445
You windbag!

1122
01:09:27.333 --> 01:09:30.046
Boom, badda-boom, boom, boom!
Hah!

1123
01:09:33.365 --> 01:09:36.711
Hercules!

1124
01:09:37.080 --> 01:09:39.826
Where are you?

1125
01:09:41.833 --> 01:09:43.979
What can we do?

1126
01:09:44.070 --> 01:09:47.144
- Where is Hercules?
- Yeah, Hercules'll save us.

1127
01:09:47.227 --> 01:09:51.017
Hercules!

1128
01:09:51.100 --> 01:09:55.568
Come out! Face me!

1129
01:09:56.892 --> 01:09:59.998
What are you doing?
Without your strength, you'll be killed.

1130
01:10:00.528 --> 01:10:02.521
There are worse things.

1131
01:10:02.604 --> 01:10:03.792
Run!

1132
01:10:03.883 --> 01:10:06.509
Wait! Stop!

1133
01:10:06.599 --> 01:10:09.911
- Hey, look! It's Hercules.
- Thank the gods!

1134
01:10:09.994 --> 01:10:12.826
- We're saved!
- So...

1135
01:10:12.910 --> 01:10:15.819
You mighty Hercules.

1136
01:10:22.257 --> 01:10:23.772
Oh!

1137
01:10:27.889 --> 01:10:30.080
Easy, horsefeathers.

1138
01:10:30.166 --> 01:10:32.553
Whoa, stop twitching.

1139
01:10:32.643 --> 01:10:35.716
Listen. Hercules is in trouble.

1140
01:10:36.437 --> 01:10:37.505
We've gotta find Phil.

1141
01:10:37.596 --> 01:10:39.982
He's the only one
who can talk some sense into him.

1142
01:10:44.347 --> 01:10:46.614
Get back, blast you!

1143
01:10:50.538 --> 01:10:53.567
- Ooh, Chihuahua.
- Zeus!

1144
01:10:55.771 --> 01:10:58.876
Come on! Hurry up!
We're shovin' off here!

1145
01:10:59.006 --> 01:11:00.434
Phil!

1146
01:11:00.604 --> 01:11:02.631
Phil, Hercules needs your help!

1147
01:11:02.720 --> 01:11:05.270
What does he need me for
when he's got friends like you?

1148
01:11:05.357 --> 01:11:09.706
- He won't listen to me.
- Good! He's finally learned something.

1149
01:11:09.792 --> 01:11:12.898
Look, I know what I did was wrong,
but this isn't about me.

1150
01:11:12.987 --> 01:11:17.095
It's about him.
If you don't help him now, Phil, he'll die.

1151
01:11:17.221 --> 01:11:19.412
I need more thunderbolts!

1152
01:11:19.498 --> 01:11:21.884
Hephaestus has been captured,
my lord.

1153
01:11:21.975 --> 01:11:24.241
Everyone's been captured.
I've been captured!

1154
01:11:24.332 --> 01:11:26.205
Hey, hey! Watch the glasses.

1155
01:11:32.240 --> 01:11:35.030
Zeusy, I'm home!

1156
01:11:35.116 --> 01:11:38.789
Hades. You're behind this!

1157
01:11:38.872 --> 01:11:40.506
You are correct, sir!

1158
01:11:44.982 --> 01:11:46.771
Flea.

1159
01:11:51.134 --> 01:11:53.924
- Hercules!
- Phil.

1160
01:11:54.010 --> 01:11:55.918
Come on, kid. Come on. Fight back.

1161
01:11:56.047 --> 01:11:58.957
Come on, you can take this bum.
This guy's a pushover. Look at him.

1162
01:11:59.043 --> 01:12:00.994
You were right all along, Phil.

1163
01:12:02.158 --> 01:12:03.946
Dreams are for rookies.

1164
01:12:04.037 --> 01:12:07.143
No, no, no, no, kid.
Givin' up is for rookies.

1165
01:12:07.232 --> 01:12:09.182
I came back
'cause I'm not quittin' on ya.

1166
01:12:09.269 --> 01:12:11.383
I'm willing to go the distance.

1167
01:12:11.466 --> 01:12:12.937
How 'bout you?

1168
01:12:15.620 --> 01:12:18.650
Me bite off head!

1169
01:12:22.330 --> 01:12:24.477
Whoa, baby!

1170
01:12:37.470 --> 01:12:39.660
Hercules! Look out!

1171
01:12:39.786 --> 01:12:42.457
Meg! No!

1172
01:12:51.051 --> 01:12:52.718
What's happening?

1173
01:12:54.367 --> 01:12:57.079
Hades' deal is broken.

1174
01:12:58.201 --> 01:13:00.272
He promised I wouldn't get hurt.

1175
01:13:00.998 --> 01:13:02.665
Meg.

1176
01:13:02.755 --> 01:13:05.425
Why did you...

1177
01:13:05.511 --> 01:13:06.742
You didn't have to...

1178
01:13:06.829 --> 01:13:11.776
Oh, people always do crazy things
when they're in love.

1179
01:13:13.021 --> 01:13:14.414
Oh, Meg.

1180
01:13:14.937 --> 01:13:16.889
Meg, I... I...

1181
01:13:17.373 --> 01:13:20.688
Are you always this articulate?

1182
01:13:23.805 --> 01:13:27.510
You haven't got much time.
You can still stop Hades.

1183
01:13:28.599 --> 01:13:30.986
I'll watch over her, kid.

1184
01:13:31.834 --> 01:13:33.709
You're gonna be all right.

1185
01:13:34.032 --> 01:13:35.905
I promise.

1186
01:13:38.266 --> 01:13:40.053
Let's go, Pegasus!

1187
01:13:42.419 --> 01:13:45.252
Hup, two, three, four.
Come on, everybody!

1188
01:13:45.415 --> 01:13:47.291
- I can't hear you!
- Oh, oh!

1189
01:13:47.972 --> 01:13:51.960
I swear to you, Hades,
when I get out of this...

1190
01:13:52.046 --> 01:13:54.835
I'm the one giving orders now, bolt boy.

1191
01:13:54.923 --> 01:13:57.232
And I think I'm gonna like it here.

1192
01:13:57.320 --> 01:13:59.990
Don't get too comfortable, Hades!

1193
01:14:01.592 --> 01:14:02.987
Hercules!

1194
01:14:03.071 --> 01:14:05.306
This ought to even the odds!

1195
01:14:07.865 --> 01:14:10.339
Yeah, Hercules! Thank you, man.

1196
01:14:10.421 --> 01:14:11.695
Get them!

1197
01:14:14.177 --> 01:14:16.127
Whoa! Hey!

1198
01:14:16.214 --> 01:14:20.201
No! Get him! Not me! Him!

1199
01:14:21.925 --> 01:14:26.230
Follow the fingers! Him!
The yutz with the horse.

1200
01:14:32.830 --> 01:14:34.584
Thank you, my boy.

1201
01:14:34.748 --> 01:14:39.215
Nice horsey! My intentions were pure!
I really was attracted to you.

1202
01:14:42.097 --> 01:14:43.405
Throw!

1203
01:14:43.495 --> 01:14:44.452
Hah!

1204
01:14:44.534 --> 01:14:47.444
Now watch your old man work!

1205
01:14:47.530 --> 01:14:48.487
Uh-oh.

1206
01:14:52.044 --> 01:14:57.034
Guys, get your titanic rears in gear
and kick some Olympian butt!

1207
01:14:57.795 --> 01:14:59.462
Whoa, is my hair out?

1208
01:15:23.600 --> 01:15:25.354
- Hah!
- Whoo-hoo!

1209
01:15:25.637 --> 01:15:27.304
Thanks a ton, Wonderboy.

1210
01:15:27.395 --> 01:15:30.065
But at least
I've got one swell consolation prize,

1211
01:15:30.151 --> 01:15:33.735
a friend of yours who's dying to see me.

1212
01:15:33.826 --> 01:15:35.253
Meg.

1213
01:16:04.623 --> 01:16:05.811
Meg.

1214
01:16:12.213 --> 01:16:13.924
Meg, no.

1215
01:16:33.264 --> 01:16:35.334
Oh, I'm sorry, kid.

1216
01:16:37.297 --> 01:16:40.162
There's some things
you just can't change.

1217
01:16:43.210 --> 01:16:44.996
Yes, I can.

1218
01:16:48.642 --> 01:16:50.910
We were so close!

1219
01:16:50.998 --> 01:16:52.425
So close.

1220
01:16:52.516 --> 01:16:54.303
We tripped at the finish line. Why?

1221
01:16:54.395 --> 01:16:58.185
Because our little nut, Meg,
has to go all noble.

1222
01:17:02.383 --> 01:17:04.976
- Where's Meg?
- Oh, look who's here.

1223
01:17:05.060 --> 01:17:07.173
Wonderboy, you are too much.

1224
01:17:07.256 --> 01:17:10.929
- Let her go.
- Get a grip.

1225
01:17:11.011 --> 01:17:13.037
Come here, come here.
Let me show you around.

1226
01:17:13.847 --> 01:17:17.312
Hmph. Well, well.
It's a small underworld after all. Huh?

1227
01:17:18.401 --> 01:17:20.275
Meg! Ahhh!

1228
01:17:20.359 --> 01:17:22.068
No, no, no. Mustn't touch.

1229
01:17:22.156 --> 01:17:24.585
You see, Meg's
running with a new crowd these days.

1230
01:17:24.711 --> 01:17:26.466
And not a very lively one, at that.

1231
01:17:28.228 --> 01:17:31.334
You like making deals.
Take me in Meg's place.

1232
01:17:31.422 --> 01:17:36.772
Well. The son of my hated rival
trapped forever in a river of death.

1233
01:17:36.855 --> 01:17:39.165
- Going once.
- Ls there a downside to this?

1234
01:17:39.252 --> 01:17:42.205
- Going twice!
- Okay, okay, okay, okay.

1235
01:17:42.288 --> 01:17:45.600
You get her out. She goes, you stay.

1236
01:17:48.440 --> 01:17:49.954
You know what slipped my mind?

1237
01:17:50.036 --> 01:17:51.823
You'll be dead
before you can get to her.

1238
01:17:51.914 --> 01:17:53.430
That's not a problem, is it?

1239
01:18:18.677 --> 01:18:19.634
Oh!

1240
01:18:20.634 --> 01:18:22.944
What's the matter with these scissors?

1241
01:18:23.031 --> 01:18:25.418
The thread won't cut.

1242
01:18:32.658 --> 01:18:35.251
This is... This is impossible!

1243
01:18:35.335 --> 01:18:38.124
You can't be alive! You'd have to be a...

1244
01:18:38.210 --> 01:18:39.562
- A god?
- A god?

1245
01:18:44.042 --> 01:18:47.594
Hercules, stop!
You can't do this to me. You can't...

1246
01:18:47.676 --> 01:18:49.867
Fine. Okay. Listen.

1247
01:18:49.953 --> 01:18:52.820
Okay. Well, I deserved that.
Herc, Herc, Herc. Can we talk?

1248
01:18:52.910 --> 01:18:54.739
Your dad, he's a fun guy, right?

1249
01:18:54.827 --> 01:18:56.941
So maybe you could
put in a word with him,

1250
01:18:57.024 --> 01:18:59.213
and he'd kinda blow this
whole thing off, you know?

1251
01:18:59.301 --> 01:19:01.775
Meg, Meg, talk to him.
A little schmooze...

1252
01:19:04.773 --> 01:19:06.603
Eww! Get away from me!
Don't touch me!

1253
01:19:06.691 --> 01:19:09.524
Get your slimy souls off me!

1254
01:19:10.286 --> 01:19:12.715
He's not gonna be happy
when he gets outta there.

1255
01:19:12.802 --> 01:19:15.548
You mean, if he gets outta there.

1256
01:19:15.638 --> 01:19:17.511
- If. If is good.
- Taxi!

1257
01:19:17.595 --> 01:19:19.742
I don't feel so good. I feel a little...

1258
01:19:43.240 --> 01:19:46.030
Wonderboy, what...

1259
01:19:46.115 --> 01:19:47.587
Why did you...

1260
01:19:48.193 --> 01:19:51.146
People always do crazy things

1261
01:19:51.229 --> 01:19:52.655
when they're in love.

1262
01:20:00.776 --> 01:20:03.130
Whoa! Hey, hey, hey! Whoo!

1263
01:20:14.397 --> 01:20:16.751
Three cheers for the mighty Hercules!

1264
01:20:16.833 --> 01:20:19.263
Oh, yeah! Flowers for everybody! Oh!

1265
01:20:32.612 --> 01:20:36.437
Hercules, we're so proud of you.

1266
01:20:37.565 --> 01:20:38.752
Mother.

1267
01:20:40.041 --> 01:20:40.998
Hah!

1268
01:20:41.079 --> 01:20:44.349
Fine work, my boy! You've done it!

1269
01:20:44.436 --> 01:20:46.745
You're a true hero.

1270
01:20:46.831 --> 01:20:50.863
You were willing to give your life
to rescue this young woman.

1271
01:20:50.946 --> 01:20:54.531
For a true hero isn't measured
by the size of his strength,

1272
01:20:54.621 --> 01:20:57.454
but by the strength of his heart.

1273
01:20:58.176 --> 01:21:02.241
Now, at last, my son,

1274
01:21:02.889 --> 01:21:05.483
you can come home.

1275
01:21:18.348 --> 01:21:22.412
Congratulations, Wonderboy.
You'll make one heck of a god.

1276
01:21:30.132 --> 01:21:34.316
Father, this is the moment
I've always dreamed of.

1277
01:21:35.245 --> 01:21:36.519
But...

1278
01:21:38.441 --> 01:21:42.951
A life without Meg,
even an immortal life,

1279
01:21:43.234 --> 01:21:45.947
would be empty.

1280
01:21:47.548 --> 01:21:48.703
I...

1281
01:21:50.024 --> 01:21:52.411
I wish to stay on Earth with her.

1282
01:21:52.500 --> 01:21:54.767
I finally know where I belong.

1283
01:22:08.479 --> 01:22:10.189
Hit it, ladies!

